Task Description (Exact Requirement)

Create a user named james on App Server 2 in the Stratos Datacenter.
Set the account expiry date to 2026-12-07, ensuring the username is created in lowercase as per standard protocol.

1ï¸âƒ£ Task Understanding
ğŸ”¹ What is the task?

The task involves creating a temporary Linux user account named james on stapp02, with a predefined account expiry date.

Once the expiry date is reached, the user account will automatically be disabled by the system.

ğŸ”¹ Why is this required in a real-world enterprise environment?

In enterprise environments like xFusionCorp Industries:

Temporary developers, consultants, or auditors often require time-bound access

Manual account removal is error-prone and may be forgotten

Expiry-based accounts:

Enforce least privilege

Reduce security risks

Ensure compliance with audit and access policies

This approach supports IAM (Identity & Access Management) best practices.

ğŸ”¹ Which server does this task apply to and why?

Server: App Server 2 (stapp02)

Reason:
The requirement explicitly states that access is needed only on App Server 2, likely because:

The developer is working on a specific application component

Limiting access prevents lateral movement across servers

