3ï¸âƒ£ Exact Commands (Step-by-Step)
ğŸ”¹ Step 1: Switch to Root (if not already)
sudo -i


Explanation:

Opens a root shell

Required for user and account policy management

Why this is best:

Avoids permission issues

Ensures full auditability

ğŸ”¹ Step 2: Create the User with Expiry Date
useradd -e 2026-12-07 james

ğŸ” Command Breakdown
Component	Meaning
useradd	Standard Linux command to create users
-e 2026-12-07	Sets account expiry date (YYYY-MM-DD format)
james	Username (lowercase as per policy)
âœ… Why this is the best choice

Native Linux tool (enterprise standard)

Expiry enforced at OS level

No cron jobs or manual cleanup required

